gomodel:SYNGO_2539  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: From the text related to figure 2, \"The co-localization of AP-1 with the pre-SV marker, synaptohysin, was tested by high-resolution 4Pi microscopy (Hell et al, 1994) and detected in control and σ1B-deficient neurons (Figure 2A). However, no or very little co-localization was observed between AP1 and the post-synaptic marker, Homer, both in WT and knockout boutons; thus supporting a predominantly pre-synaptic localization of AP-1 (Figure 2A)\".. Experimental description: M&M: \"Hippocampal cell culture. Primary hippocampal neurons were isolated from P0-P2 pups of wild type or AP1-σ1B-deficient mice, dissociated by trypsin digestion and plated on Poly-D-lysine-coated glass coverslips.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2539" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

